⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Grushenka
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦Grushenka:BKZ:a4dd97⟧

WHO   — Grushenka — the earth · the contested woman
WHAT  — The earthly fire of the plot and its surprising tenderness: scorned and scheming at first, she turns toward real love and redemption with Dmitri.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Karamazov earth needs a woman as ‘broad’ as the men — capable of cruelty and of a sudden, saving generosity (the ‘onion’ tale).
HOW   — By beauty, pride, a long-nursed grievance, and a heart that proves larger than her schemes.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I meant only to torment them, and found I could love after all — even a wicked woman has once given an onion, and may be pulled out by it.

